    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-26T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="213"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00/4–2654: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 213<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France (<persName corresp="#p_DILLONCD1"
                            type="from">Dillon</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d213fn1">Repeated to Brussels and Geneva.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-26T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 26, 1954—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4065. The Secretary requested that following be added to report of his meeting
                    with <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d213fn2">Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName> was in Paris to attend the North Atlantic Council
                        meetings, Apr. 23.</note> reported in <gloss target="#t_Secto1"
                        >Secto</gloss> 11.<note n="3" xml:id="d213fn3">Telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 11 from Paris, Apr. 24, reported on
                            <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName>’ conversation with
                            <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> concerning matters
                        relating to the European Defense Community; for the text, see <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v05p1#pg_949">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, Part
                            1, p. 949</ref>.</note> During general conversation between <persName
                        corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> and Secretary regarding delays in
                    bringing about unification of Europe, <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1"
                        >Spaak</persName> said that over-generous policy by the US in the past must
                    take a substantial part of the blame for the lack of progress towards the
                    unification of Europe. <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> said the
                    US missed a golden opportunity when at the outset of the Marshall Plan they did
                    not make all Marshall aid contingent upon the creation of a unified political
                    community in Europe.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DILLONCD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dillon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
